## Overview

SENSE is a **model-agnostic AI evolution platform** that combines reasoning, grounding, self-modification, and autonomous learning into a cohesive system. Unlike traditional AI agents, SENSE can:

- ğŸ”„ **Self-evolve** through genetic algorithms (GRPO)
- ğŸ§ª **Ground itself** in reality via three-tier verification (Synthetic, Real-world, Experiential)
- ğŸ”§ **Create tools** dynamically by crystallizing repeated successful behaviors
- ğŸ¤– **Execute autonomously** with continuous self-improvement
- ğŸ›¡ï¸ **Operate safely** through whitelisted command execution
- ğŸŒ **Support any LLM** (OpenAI, Anthropic, Ollama, local models)

---

## ğŸš€ Quick Start

### Installation

```bash
# Clone repository
git clone https://github.com/taeddings/SENSE.git
cd SENSE

# Install dependencies
pip install -e .

# Verify installation
sense --help
```

### Basic Usage

```bash
# Solve a single task
sense --mode single --task "Calculate 15 * 23"

# Start autonomous self-evolution
sense --mode continuous

# Run GRPO evolution for 10 generations
sense --mode evolve --generations 10

# Launch interactive dashboard
sense-dashboard

# Start API server
sense-api --port 8000
```

